All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.ContainerListener, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class UMLGUI
extends javax.swing.JFrame
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.ContainerListener

The primary Graphical User Interface which includes all other components. It even has a menu bar. It supports shortcut keys also. Using it is as simple as using a normal JFrame (the only difference is this JFrame is shipped with everything you may need! 

 UMLGUI gui = new UMLGUI();
 gui.setVisible(true);
You may enable the debug mode of ALL other component by triggering UMLGUI.debuging = true;. It's kind of a shortcut to debug globally.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Dao Hoang Son
See Also:
debuging, Serialized Form

Method Detail

actionPerformed

public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent e)
Main handler for all actions.
Supported actions:
  • exit: Simply dispose the JFrame
  • load: Do the load procedure by calling doLoad(String)
  • image: Do the save image procedure by calling doImage(String)
  • generate: Do the generate source procedure by calling doGenerate(String)
  • clear: Confirm and clear the entire diagram
  • new: Create new structure
    • Class: use ClassForm
    • Interface: use InterfaceForm
    • Property: use ListForm.select(java.awt.Frame, String, Structure[], String) allowing user to choose a Class or a Interface before using PropertyForm
    • Method: use ListForm.select(java.awt.Frame, String, Structure[], String) allowing user to choose a Class or a Interface before using MethodForm
    • Argument: user ListForm.select(java.awt.Frame, String, Structure[], String) 2 times before using ArgumentForm

Specified by:
actionPerformed in interface java.awt.event.ActionListener

doLoad

private void doLoad(java.lang.String title)
Processes the Load request.
At first, display a directory chooser to select the source directory. And then temporary disable drawing on change functionality of diagram (for performance reason). Create new parser to parse the directory recursively. Finally, trigger the diagram to update the display

Parameters:
title - the title of the action
See Also:
Diagram.cfg_draw_on_change

doImage

private void doImage(java.lang.String title)
Processes the save image request.
At first, use a file chooser to allow selecting a file to save image to. Use the saving functionality from the diagram to export image.

Parameters:
title - the title of the action
See Also:
Diagram.saveImage(java.awt.image.ImageObserver), DiagramImageObserver

doGenerate

private void doGenerate(java.lang.String title)
Processes the source generating functionality.
At first, display a directory chooser allowing select the destination directory for generating. And then, obviously, create a code generator to generate to the specified directory

Parameters:
title - the title of the action
